result.execSummary:
The defendant Jamal Taveon Clements was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jamal Taveon Clements is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jamal Taveon Clements was found guilty of 1st-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety [Modifiers: Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(1).
  • Jamal Taveon Clements was found guilty of Carry Concealed Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.23(2).
  • Jamal Taveon Clements was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jamal Taveon Clements in court with attorney Daniel Gordon Mitchell.  Defendant Jamal Taveon Clements in custody.  Nathaniel E Adamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court finds State has complied with victim notification requirements. Statements made as to sentencing.  

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 8 YEARS (CONCURRENT TO COUNTS 3 & 4), with credit for 320 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 4 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4 YEARS.  The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".
AS TO COUNT 3: The Court sentenced the defendant to 6 MONTHS (CONCURRENT TO COUNTS 1 & 4). 
AS TO COUNT 4: The Court sentenced the defendant to 6 MONTHS (CONCURRENT TO COUNTS 1 & 3).
Court sets restitution at $0.   
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges. 
As to all costs and surcharges, Court orders DOC shall collect up to 25% of prison wages.  Remaining balance to be paid during the period of extended supervision.  Unpaid amount to covert to a civil judgment.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

At the hour of 2:00pm the jury returned and, by their foreperson, brought in a verdict of GUILTY as to COUNT 1 which was then read.  As to penalty enhancer, jury answers the question "YES."  Court polled and discharged the jury.  Verdict received and filed.  Court granted state's motion for judgment on the verdict and denied defense motion for judgment not withstanding the verdict.  Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction.  Court orders defendant REMANDED pending sentencing.  Matter is scheduled for sentencing on 2/12/16 at 8:30am in Br. 35.
